 Sun . Apr . 14th War news look a bit bright and this morn we are hold Fritz back , but the casualti on both side must be enorm . Georg Lawson , the Billiard marker , finish up at his job today , had a few word with the " Food Control " . He and I went into Warminst after Dinner . The Depot Band was play at the Town Hall , and tho ? it was bitter cold a good crowd gather to listen to the Music . We had some Biscuit and Tea at the new " Y.M. " went for a stroll and had some more Tea and Sandwich at the Town Hall . Then we went to the Methodist Church . It was quit home and I enjoy it much better than " the Minster " servic . Sun 14 ( cont ) After the Servic we attend a Sing-Song in the School-Room . I met Sgt Matheson there . A number of Ladi were present and hand round Tea and Cake . They gave us an invit to attend a Social on Tuesday night , but I wo n't be abl to go as I shall be work . Return to Camp about 9.30 . Com . Letter 19 to B.E. Mon . Apr . 15 Wet , miser day . Arthur Foster is crook and the M.O. mark him " no duty" . " Tobi " Nicholson is carri on his Job .
